cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.SY

This paper involves deep reinforcement learning in partially observable 3D environments, which suggests it could belong to several sub-categories. The use of neural memory architecture and CNN feature vectors suggests it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). The focus on spatially structured memory and mapping suggests it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the use of ego-motion measurements suggests it could belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, and cs.SY, in that order.
